cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.PL. 

The paper deals with algorithms for computing visibility polygons in computational geometry, which is a core topic in cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The implementation and experimental evaluations of the algorithms involve data structures (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and graph theory (cs.GR). The algorithms also deal with planar polygons and arrangements, which are topics in cs.PL (Discrete Geometry and Combinatorics).
